msgid "# Session and Seat Management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/config/session-management.md:6
msgid ""
"Session and seat management is not necessary for every setup, but it can be "
"used to safely create temporary runtime directories, provide access to "
"hardware devices and multi-seat capabilities, and control system shutdown."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/config/session-management.md:8
msgid "## D-Bus"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/config/session-management.md:12
msgid ""
"D-Bus is an IPC (inter-process communication) mechanism used by userspace "
"software in Linux. D-Bus can provide a system bus and/or a session bus, the "
"latter being specific to a user session."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/config/session-management.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"- To provide a system bus, you should [enable](./services/index.md) the `dbus`\n"
"   service. This might require a system reboot to work properly.\n"
"- To provide a session bus, you can start a given program (usually a window\n"
"   manager or interactive shell) with\n"
"   [dbus-run-session(1)](https://man.voidlinux.org/dbus-run-session.1). Most\n"
"   desktop environments, if launched through an adequate display manager, will\n"
"   launch a D-Bus session themselves.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/config/session-management.md:23
msgid ""
"Note that some software assumes the presence of a system bus, while other "
"software assumes the presence of a session bus."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/config/session-management.md:25 src/config/power-management.md:11
msgid "## elogind"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/config/session-management.md:30
msgid ""
"[elogind(8)](https://man.voidlinux.org/elogind.8) manages user logins and "
"system power, as a standalone version of `systemd-logind`. elogind provides "
"necessary features for most desktop environments and Wayland compositors. It "
"can also be one of the mechanisms for rootless [Xorg](./graphical-session/"
"xorg.md)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/config/session-management.md:33
msgid ""
"Please read the \"[Power Management](./power-management.md)\" section for "
"things to consider before installing elogind."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/config/session-management.md:36
msgid ""
"To make use of its features, install the `elogind` package and make sure the "
"[system D-Bus](#d-bus) is enabled. You might need to log out and in again."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/config/session-management.md:39
msgid ""
"If you're having any issues with elogind, [enable](./services/index.md) its "
"service, as waiting for a D-Bus activation can lead to issues."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: src/config/session-management.md:42
msgid ""
"There is an alternative D-Bus configuration which takes advantage of elogind "
"for features such as seat detection. It requires installing the `dbus-"
"elogind`, `dbus-elogind-libs` and `dbus-elogind-x11` packages."
msgstr ""
